        <TextBlock x:Name="Paragraph" HorizontalAlignment="Left" TextWrapping="Wrap" VerticalAlignment="Top" Margin="4,27,0,0" FontFamily="Bebas Kai" FontSize="16" Width="421"><Run Text="Logical operators are used to combine multiple relational operators into a larger composite condition. "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="There is the &quot;OR&quot; (||) , &quot;AND&quot; (&amp;&amp;), and &quot;NOT&quot; (!). "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="&quot;And&quot; (&amp;&amp;) is only a true value if the conditions on both sides of the operator are true. "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="&quot;Or&quot; (||) is only false when the conditions on both sides of the operator are false. "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="&quot;NOT&quot; (!) reverses the logic of the single condition. "/><LineBreak/><Run/><LineBreak/><Run/><LineBreak/><Run/></TextBlock>


